This file defines the main `IntegrationsPage` component for the DocMed dashboard. It's responsible for displaying and managing connected repository pairs.

## Purpose

The `IntegrationsPage` component serves as the central hub for users to view, add, and manage integrations between different Git repositories. It fetches a list of configured repository pairs and presents them to the user, along with options to add new integrations or handle potential configuration errors.

## Key Features

*   **Authentication:** Utilizes Clerk's `auth()` to get the current `userId`, which is crucial for fetching user-specific repository pairs.
*   **Repository Pair Listing:** Calls `listRepoPairs(userId!)` to retrieve an array of repository pairs associated with the authenticated user.
*   **Error Handling:** Includes a `try...catch` block to gracefully handle potential errors during the `listRepoPairs` call. Any errors are displayed to the user in a prominent warning banner.
*   **Conditional Rendering:**
    *   Displays a "Firebase error" banner if `configError` is present.
    *   Shows a "No repository pairs yet" message with a `GitBranch` icon when no integrations are configured and there are no errors.
    *   Renders a list of `RepoPairCard` components if repository pairs are found.
*   **UI Components:** Integrates `RepoPairCard` to display individual repository pair details and `AddPairButton` for initiating the addition of new integrations.

## Usage Example

This component is rendered as a page within the Next.js application at the `/dashboard/integrations` route. It automatically fetches data upon navigation and displays the relevant UI based on the presence of integrations and potential errors.

```tsx
// app/dashboard/integrations/page.tsx

import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { listRepoPairs } from "@/lib/repo-pairs";
import { RepoPairCard } from "./_components/RepoPairCard";
import { AddPairButton } from "./_components/AddPairButton";
import { GitBranch } from "lucide-react";

export default async function IntegrationsPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();

  let pairs: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof listRepoPairs>> = [];
  let configError: string | null = null;

  try {
    pairs = await listRepoPairs(userId!); // Fetches user's repo pairs
  } catch (err) {
    configError = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
  }

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col h-full p-8">
      <div className="flex items-start justify-between mb-8 gap-4">
        <div>
          <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground tracking-tight">
            Integrations
          </h1>
          <p className="text-muted-foreground text-sm mt-1">
            Connect repository pairs — DocMed reads from the target and writes
            healed docs to the doc repo.
          </p>
        </div>
        <AddPairButton /> {/* Button to add new integrations */}
      </div>

      {/* Error banner */} 
      {configError && (
        <div className="mb-6 rounded-lg border border-yellow-500/20 bg-yellow-500/5 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-yellow-400">
          <p className="font-medium">Firebase error</p>
          <p className="mt-1 font-mono text-xs opacity-80">{configError}</p>
        </div>
      )}

      {/* Empty state */}
      {!configError && pairs.length === 0 && (
        <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center flex-1 gap-3 text-center">
          <div className="size-12 rounded-xl bg-muted flex items-center justify-center">
            <GitBranch className="size-5 text-muted-foreground" />
          </div>
          <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            No repository pairs yet. Add one to get started.
          </p>
        </div>
      )}

      {/* List of integrations */}
      {pairs.length > 0 && (
        <div className="flex flex-col gap-4">
          {pairs.map((pair) => (
            <RepoPairCard key={pair.id} pair={pair} />
          ))}
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}
```
